On health now and the covid 19 pandemic continues to impact the lives of millions of people around the world, and in the wake of the rising number of infections so is the number of fatalities from the disease&hellip; deaths that have left friends of the deceased in pain and agony. And as families continue to mourn their loved ones, the ripple effect of these deaths has not spared yet another lot of clerics, who have to perform burial rights for their congregants or even offer religious rights for the dying. And as Gloria Milimu reports this increase in the number of deaths has left clerics from Siaya county traumatized posing a threat to their mental wellbeing